# 6. 残されていた記録

An: I'm home!
Akito: Hey, Ken.
An's Father: Ah, you're all back...
An: Yup! Wait, where is everyone...? Did we not get any customers today?
An's Father: A big group was here for a bit after an event had got out and left just a little while ago. This might be it for the bar tonight.
Taiga: What? You're calling it quits while a woman in her eighties is still working herself to the bone?
An's Father: Hm? Oh, you're here too.
Taiga: Hey, I was acting as their guide today.
An's Father: Haha. Is that so? By the way, how was our dear, old owner?
Taiga: Good. Honestly, I'm having a hard time seeing her lose to Father Time at this point...
An's Father: Haha. Right?!
Taiga: But I think it was worth the trip. It looked like they managed to figure out something.
Kohane: Thank you very much, Taiga.
Kohane: I have a slightly better idea of what happened during RAD WEEKEND because of what you did for us.
Taiga: You think so? In that case, you're welcome.
An's Father: (I've seen this look on Taiga's face before.)
An's Father: (It's like...)
???: Taiga, Ken, let's go!
Taiga: Relax, will you? The stage isn't going anywhere.
???: All I want to do right now is sing. So hurry!
Taiga: Alright, I get it. Be right there...
An's Father: ...
An's Father: (So that's it...)
An's Father: (Taiga wants Kohane and her to...)
An's Father: (This has to be why he was willing to show them COL.)
An's Father: (Maybe not consciously, but if Taiga's going to make a move like that...)
An's Father: (It's time for me to act as well.)
An's Father: An, switch the sign to “Closed”.
An: Huh? You sure?
An's Father: It's about time you guys saw this.
Kohane: See what?
An's Father: This.
Akito: Hm? A DVD...?
Taiga: A DVD...?
Toya: Mind if we have a look at it?
An's Father: Yeah, be my guest.
An: There's something written on the cover... “RAD WEEKEND”...?
An: No way! Is this really...?!
An's Father: Yes. It's a video of RAD WEEKEND.
Taiga: What...?!
Kohane: What?! B-But...
An: Dad, you said there weren't any videos of what happened...!
An's Father: I was asked to hold on to this one and forgot about it.
Taiga: Hold on to it? What are you talking about, Ken?
Taiga: No cameras were allowed. Period. Granny even agreed to those terms.
An's Father: She's the one who took this.
Taiga: What...?
An's Father: Anyway, this'll show you what happened during RAD WEEKEND from start to finish.
An's Father: Wanna see?
Kohane: Y-Yes...! Please!!
An: We have a screen and projector for the stage area, so I'll go get those set up!
Kohane: Oh, I'll help...!
Toya: You two get the projector set up. We'll unfurl the screen while you do.
An: Okay! Let's get to it!
Taiga: Hey, Ken...
Taiga: Why'd Granny take this? She's the owner. She's supposed to enforce these kinds of rules.
An's Father: She said Nagi asked her to do this.
Taiga: Nagi asked her...?
Kohane: Excuse me, can you tell me where the DVD player is...? Oh...
An's Father: Nagi apparently said, “This will help someone down the road, so please record it for us in secret.”
An's Father: However, you were gone before she even had a chance to tell you about this...
Taiga: Nagi...
Kohane: (Wait, Nagi's...)
An: Oh, Nagi Kotaki. She's Uncle Taiga's little sister.
An: She, Uncle Taiga and Dad used to be on the same team.
Kohane: (Taiga's little sister made this DVD...?)
Kohane: E-Excuse me...!
Kohane: Th-Thank you both very much!
Kohane: As you know, I've been wanting to learn more about what happened during RAD WEEKEND...
Kohane: And I'd really like it if you could give Nagi my regards as well!
Taiga: Alright... I'll tell her the next time I see her.
Akito: Hey, you find us a DVD player yet?
Kohane: Oh, right...! Do you have one we can borrow?
An's Father: Yeah, sure. Use this one...
Kohane: Thank you!
Toya: Shiraishi, the screen's all set up.
An: Great! That means it's showtime...!
An: You guys ready...?
Kohane: Yeah!
